nhouse.io/ocmiinc/jobs/4891263008","published_at":"2025-09-11T16:54:43-04:00","department":{"name":"Scheduling","id":4031001008,"path":[]},"is_featured":false}]},"featuredPosts":{"data":[{"id":5174767008,"title":"Mechanical Cost Estimator","location":"Dallas, TX","payRange":null,"content":"\u003cdiv\u003eAt OCMI, our core values—One Team, Curiosity, Meaningful Service, and Integrity—drive everything we do. Founded in 1982 and still privately owned, we've become one of the nation's fastest-growing construction management consultancies. Serving markets across federal, education, hospitality, healthcare, technology, and commercial sectors, we offer comprehensive services including cost management, project management, scheduling, and project controls. Most importantly, our teams are passionate about supporting each other and making a difference in the communities we serve. \nWe're thrilled to welcome a mechanically focused Cost Estimator to our Dallas office! This flexible, hybrid role offers you the opportunity to be a key member of our cost estimating team, where you'll have the chance to learn and grow your career with a passionate team of cost estimating and construction management professionals.\nIf you're an experienced cost professional seeking a company that offers growth, flexibility, and an exceptional culture, we encourage you to apply now. A recruiter will respond to your resume within five business days. \nResponsibilities:\n\nProvide detailed quantity take-off and preliminary pricing for a variety of construction project types.  \nReview and interpret construction drawings to understand the overall project scope.\nSupport development of comprehensive cost estimates/models communicating the client’s project and strategic goals.\nFacilitate document control, file management, and project collaboration.\nEnsure a quality product is presented to the client by adhering to QA/QC procedures.\nActively research, solicit and develop sources/vendors to compile and maintain the accuracy of cost information.\nCommunicate effectively through clear and concise means appropriate to the project goals.\n\nQualifications:\n\n3-5 years of cost estimating experience in vertical construction/engineering projects preferred.\nMechanical/plumbing cost estimating experience required.\nAbility to understand and accurately interpret construction documents (drawings, specifications).\nProficient user of On-Screen Takeoff (OST) software or similar quantity takeoff software preferred.\nWorking knowledge of Microsoft Excel\nStrong written and verbal communication skills\nA bachelor’s degree in construction, engineering, or architecture, or 2 years of applicable construction trade experience in lieu of a degree, is preferred.\n\nBenefits include:\n\nHybrid flexibility depending on position.\nCompany-sponsored Medical/Dental/Vision and Life Insurance\n401K Program with a Company Match\nPaid Holidays / Sick Leave / Vacation Accrual\nCompany Team Building, Employee Events, and a fun, people-first environment\n\n \nCompensation: $105,000 -125,000\nOCMI, Inc. (OCMI) is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. OCMI does not discriminate based on race, color, creed, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, religion, national origin, disability, ancestry, marital status, veteran status, medical condition, or any protected category prohibited by local, state, or federal laws. \n#LI-EJ1\u003c/div\u003e","absolute_url":"https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/ocmiinc/jobs/5174767008"}]},"board":{"name":"OCMI, Inc.","public_url":"https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/ocmiinc","content":"","redirect_to":null},"departments":[{"id":4025581008,"value":4025581008,"name":"Cost Management","label":"Cost Management","children":[]},{"id":4025580008,"value":4025580008,"name":"Project Management","label":"Project Management","children":[]},{"id":4031001008,"value":4031001008,"name":"Scheduling","label":"Scheduling","children":[]}],"recentlyLiveDepartments":[{"id":4025581008,"value":4025581008,"name":"Cost Management","label":"Cost Management"},{"id":4025580008,"value":4025580008,"name":"Project Management","label":"Project Management"},{"id":4031001008,"value":4031001008,"name":"Scheduling","label":"Scheduling"}],"offices":[{"id":4024878008,"value":4024878008,"name":"Dallas","label":"Dallas","children":[]},{"id":4026405008,"value":4026405008,"name":"Remote","label":"Remote","children":[]},{"id":4020253008,"value":4020253008,"name":"San Diego","label":"San Diego","children":[]},{"id":4024876008,"value":4024876008,"name":"Seattle","label":"Seattle","children":[]},{"id":4024875008,"value":4024875008,"name":"Washington, D.C.","label":"Washington, D.C.","children":[{"id":4066542008,"value":4066542008,"name":"Auburn, AL","label":"Auburn, AL","children":[]}]}],"departmentIds":[],"officeIds":[],"customFieldFilters":{},"urlToken":"ocmiinc","customFields":[{"id":5936768008,"name":"Work Arrangement","priority":2,"value_type":"multi_select","options":[{"id":10020011008,"name":"In-office","priority":0},{"id":10020008008,"name":"Hybrid","priority":1},{"id":10020009008,"name":"Remote","priority":2},{"id":10020012008,"name":"On-site","priority":3}]}],"url":"http://job-boards.greenhouse.io/ocmiinc"}},"actionData":null,"errors":null}};</script><script type="module" async="">import "https://job-boards.cdn.greenhouse.io/assets/manifest-b3324b8e.js";
